</table>
</div>

<div data-lang="en" id="plains-en">
<div class="collapsible"><div class="collapsible-toggle" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="true"><h3>🌾 Plains</h3><span class="toggle-icon">▶</span></div><div class="collapsible-body open"><div class="collapsible-body-inner">

<p>The best starting biome! Open terrain, good visibility, fewer surprises.</p>

<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Property</th><th>Details</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Temperature</td><td>Moderate — no freezing risk</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Torch special</td><td><strong>Torches NEVER burn out on Plains!</strong> The only biome where this is true</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Mob spawning</td><td>Normal — nighttime defense required</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Resources</td><td>Wheat, horse, cow, sheep — good food source</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Villages</td><td>Most commonly spawn on Plains!</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="info-box">💡 <strong>Starter tip:</strong> If your world spawn is on Plains, stay there for the first few days — torches won't burn out, which greatly helps with defense!</div>

</div></div></div>
</div>

<div data-lang="en" id="forest-en">
<div class="collapsible"><div class="collapsible-toggle" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="true"><h3>🌲 Forest</h3><span class="toggle-icon">▶</span></div><div class="collapsible-body open"><div class="collapsible-body-inner">

<p>Abundant wood supply, but dense vegetation reduces visibility and lets mobs sneak up on you.</p>

<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Property</th><th>Details</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Temperature</td><td>Moderate</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Resources</td><td>Oak, birch, spruce — plenty of wood; mushrooms; apples</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Dangers</td><td>Reduced visibility → mobs can get very close</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Torches</td><td>Burn out after 3 days (in Hardcore mode)</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="warning-box">⚠️ <strong>Be careful at night in the Forest!</strong> Zombies and spiders attack from very close range between the trees. Defend with fences and a well-lit base.</div>

</div></div></div>
</div>

<div data-lang="en" id="taiga-en">
<div class="collapsible"><div class="collapsible-toggle" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="true"><h3>🌨 Taiga</h3><span class="toggle-icon">▶</span></div><div class="collapsible-body open"><div class="collapsible-body-inner">

<p>Cold biome — the temperature system matters most here. You can freeze quickly at night and in rain.</p>

<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Property</th><th>Details</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Temperature</td><td><strong>Cold</strong> — freezing risk at night!</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Resources</td><td>Spruce wood, wolves, berry bushes</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Snowy Taiga</td><td>Even colder — walking through snow slows you down</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Preventing freezing</td><td>Warm food (stew, porridge), stay near fire, warm clothing</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="warning-box">🌡️ <strong>Body temperature:</strong> Drops fast in Taiga at night + rain. If it hits zero, you die of cold! Always carry stew or warm soup, and stay near fire at night.</div>

</div></div></div>
</div>

<div data-lang="en" id="desert-en">
<div class="collapsible"><div class="collapsible-toggle" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="true"><h3>🏜 Desert</h3><span class="toggle-icon">▶</span></div><div class="collapsible-body open"><div class="collapsible-body-inner">

<p>Hot, dry biome with a unique enemy — the Desert Guardian. Contains a rare structure (Desert Guardian Tower).</p>

<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Property</th><th>Details</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Temperature</td><td>Warm during the day — heat stroke possible</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Unique mob</td><td><strong>Desert Guardian</strong> — fast, strong, rare drops</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Structure</td><td><strong>Desert Guardian Tower</strong> — rare loot chests</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Resources</td><td>Sand, sandstone, cactus, dead bushes</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Water</td><td>No natural water source — bring your own!</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="warning-box">🏜 <strong>Desert Guardian:</strong> Don't underestimate it! Fast and strong. Mithril+ gear recommended for attacking the Tower.</div>

</div></div></div>
</div>

<div data-lang="en" id="swamp-en">
<div class="collapsible"><div class="collapsible-toggle" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="true"><h3>🌿 Swamp</h3><span class="toggle-icon">▶</span></div><div class="collapsible-body open"><div class="collapsible-body-inner">

<p>Wet, dark biome with witches and mud caves. Poison is a serious threat here.</p>

<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Property</th><th>Details</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Temperature</td><td>Moderate but wet — standing in water cools you down</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Unique danger</td><td><strong>Witches</strong> — throw poison potions; hostile fairies</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Resources</td><td>Clay, lily pads, swamp wood</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Caves</td><td>Mud caves — water-filled, hard to navigate</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="warning-box">🧪 <strong>Witch:</strong> If it throws a poison potion at you, immediately drink milk (antidote) or flee! Poison kills quickly at low HP.</div>

</div></div></div>
</div>

<div data-lang="en" id="mountains-en">
<div class="collapsible"><div class="collapsible-toggle" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="true"><h3>⛰ Mountains</h3><span class="toggle-icon">▶</span></div><div class="collapsible-body open"><div class="collapsible-body-inner">

<p>Spectacular but dangerous biome — falling and freezing are the two main risks. In return, rare ores and stones can be found on the surface.</p>

<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Property</th><th>Details</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Temperature</td><td><strong>Cold</strong> at high altitude — freezing risk</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Fall risk</td><td>Steep slopes — risk of slipping and falling</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Resources</td><td>Stone, gravel, snow; occasionally surface ore veins</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Blood Moon effect</td><td>Y&gt;100: Nausea+Weakness — <strong>get down from the heights!</strong></td></tr>
</table>

<div class="info-box">⛏ <strong>Mountain mining:</strong> Steep cliff faces sometimes expose surface ores (copper, silver) — worth scanning the rock walls before going underground.</div>

</div></div></div>
</div>

<div data-lang="en" id="jungle-en">
<div class="collapsible"><div class="collapsible-toggle" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="true"><h3>🌴 Jungle</h3><span class="toggle-icon">▶</span></div><div class="collapsible-body open"><div class="collapsible-body-inner">

<p>Dense, complex biome with lots of natural resources — but hard to navigate and threatened by poisonous creatures.</p>

<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Property</th><th>Details</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Temperature</td><td>Warm and humid</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Unique danger</td><td>Poisonous spiders, jungle creeper variants</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Resources</td><td><strong>Bamboo</strong>, banana, cocoa beans, coconut palm — unique foods</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Navigation</td><td>Very dense — easy to get lost</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="info-box">🍌 <strong>Jungle foods:</strong> Bananas, coconuts, and cocoa beans are only found in the Jungle. Needed for special recipes if you have food preparation skill (or v0.9.0+ professions)!</div>

</div></div></div>
</div>

<div data-lang="en" id="mushroom-en">
<div class="collapsible"><div class="collapsible-toggle" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="true"><h3>🍄 Mushroom Islands</h3><span class="toggle-icon">▶</span></div><div class="collapsible-body open"><div class="collapsible-body-inner">

<p>Unique, rare biome — normal mobs don't spawn here! However, MITE:BE adds its own unique structure to these islands.</p>

<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Property</th><th>Details</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Mob spawning</td><td><strong>Normal mobs DO NOT spawn!</strong> — but the MITE Combat Tower does</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Unique mob</td><td>Mooshroom — can be milked, gives mushroom stew</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Structure</td><td><strong>Mushroom Forest Combat Tower</strong> — advanced loot, strong enemies</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Resources</td><td>Giant mushrooms, mycelium soil</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="warning-box">⚔️ <strong>Combat Tower:</strong> The unique MITE structure of Mushroom Islands. Tough monsters, rare reward chests. Mithril+ gear required for full clearance.</div>

</div></div></div>
</div>

<div data-lang="en" id="ocean-en">
<div class="collapsible"><div class="collapsible-toggle" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="true"><h3>🌊 Ocean</h3><span class="toggle-icon">▶</span></div><div class="collapsible-body open"><div class="collapsible-body-inner">

<p>Vast water surface — the temperature system and drowning are the main threats. Ideal for fishing and underwater mining.</p>

<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Property</th><th>Details</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Temperature</td><td>Being in water cools you — <strong>rapid freezing risk in cold biomes!</strong></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Main danger</td><td>Drowning, temperature loss, underwater enemies</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Resources</td><td>Fish, squid, coral, sand, gravel</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Fishing</td><td>Better catch rates with the Fishing skill</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="info-box">🎣 <strong>Fishing tip:</strong> Standing on the ocean shore is the easiest way to fish — no need to go in the water! Water Breathing potion is mandatory for deep-sea caves.</div>

</div></div></div>
</div>

<div data-lang="en" id="nether-en">
<div class="collapsible"><div class="collapsible-toggle" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="true"><h3>🔥 Nether</h3><span class="toggle-icon">▶</span></div><div class="collapsible-body open"><div class="collapsible-body-inner">

<p>Entering the Nether requires serious preparation — but the most important materials (Blaze Rod, Wither Rose, Mithril+ smelting) can only be obtained here.</p>

<div class="warning-box">🔥 <strong>Nether entry requirements:</strong> Mithril Pickaxe (for mining Obsidian) + Obsidian Ingot Mold + Flint and Steel. Fire Resistance potion strongly recommended!</div>

<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Property</th><th>Details</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Temperature</td><td>Extreme heat — heat stroke risk</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Unique danger</td><td>Fire Elemental: <strong>3% instant death if you're on fire when it attacks!</strong> Fire Resistance mandatory</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Portal mechanic</td><td>Obsidian portal at bedrock level → Pillager Fortress (v0.9.0)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Nether Fortress</td><td>Blaze Rod (heat level 4 smelting), Wither Rose, Nether Wart</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Blaze</td><td>Blaze Rod required for Adamantium smelting!</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Wither Skeleton</td><td>Drops Wither Rose — required for summoning the Wither boss</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="info-box">🌋 <strong>Lava bucket:</strong> Fuel for heat level 3 (Mithril smelting). Fill it up in the Nether — there's no lava source at home!</div>

</div></div></div>
</div>

<div data-lang="en" id="underground-en">
<div class="collapsible"><div class="collapsible-toggle" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="true"><h3>⛏ Underground World</h3><span class="toggle-icon">▶</span></div><div class="collapsible-body open"><div class="collapsible-body-inner">

<p>MITE:BE's most complex "biome" — below Y=0 there are special layers with their own mobs, structures, and rare resources.</p>

<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Layer (Y)</th><th>Block</th><th>Mobs</th><th>Special</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Y 0 – (-30)</td><td>Hardstone</td><td>Revenant, Wight</td><td>Hardstone ore, special caves</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Y (-30) – (-60)</td><td>Ancient Stone</td><td>Wight Guard, Skeleton Lord</td><td>Crystal caves, Mithril ore</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Y (-60)+</td><td>Primordial Stone</td><td>Revenant, special enemies</td><td>Adamantium ore, mysterious ruins</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="warning-box">💀 <strong>Skeleton Lord:</strong> Strong mini-boss in the deeper layers. Valuable drops but hard to defeat. Mithril+ gear required.</div>

<div class="info-box">🔮 <strong>Underground Ruins (v0.9.0):</strong> Randomly generated ruins are found throughout the cave system — with loot chests and Knowledge Books!</div>

<h4>Underground Mining Strategy</h4>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Hardstone layer:</strong> War hammer crushing on Hardstone blocks → 12 ore particles</li>
  <li><strong>Vs Revenant:</strong> Silver weapons are effective — Smite enchantment also helps</li>
  <li><strong>Vs Wight Guard:</strong> Fast and strong — avoid frontal combat, use trap strategy</li>
  <li><strong>Way back:</strong> Mark your path! It's easy to get lost in the depths</li>
</ul>

</div></div></div>
</div>

